    "content": "return ( ); \"use client\"; interface PlaybookPageLayoutProps children: ReactNode; : PlaybookPageLayoutProps) return ( /* Content */ children /* Footer */ ); // ✅ Server Component by default return ( /* Header Block */ Operations Playbook Meeting Cadence Our Rhythm of Communication &amp; Alignment /* Meeting Overview */ Meeting Overview Meeting Frequency Duration Attendees Owner Daily Standup Daily (async) 5 min (SOD/EOD) All team Each person Weekly Ops + Marketing Weekly 30 min Ops + Marketing Ops Coord Weekly All-Hands Weekly 30-45 min All departments Ops Coord Ad-Hoc / As-Needed As needed 15-30 min Relevant people Requester Client Weekly Check-in Weekly per client 30 min Ops + Client Ops Coord Monthly Review Monthly 45-60 min Founder + 1 Founder Quarterly Planning Quarterly 2-3 hours All team Founder /* 1. Daily Standup */ 1 . Daily Standup (Async via Lark) SOD (Start of Day) — Post by 9:00 AM: Top 3 priorities for today Any blockers or help needed EOD (End of Day) — Post by 6:00 PM: What got done today What&apos;s carrying over to tomorrow Any issues or wins to flag /* 2. Weekly Ops + Marketing Sync */ 2 . Weekly Ops + Marketing Sync When: Every Monday, 9:00 AM (30 min) Who: Operations Coordinator + Marketing Specialist Purpose: Align on client deliverables, content calendars, and handoffs between ops and marketing tasks. Agenda: Time Topic Details 5 min Client Status Quick Check Any urgent client issues or updates 10 min This Week&apos;s Deliverables What&apos;s due, who&apos;s doing what, dependencies 10 min Handoffs &amp; Blockers Items passing between Ops ↔ Marketing, any blockers 5 min Action Items Confirm who does what by when Required Output: Brief notes in Ops + Marketing Lark channel /* 3. Weekly All-Hands */ 3 . Weekly All-Hands (All Departments) When: Every Friday, 10:00 AM (30-45 min) Who: All team members (Ops, Marketing, Web Dev, Finance, HR) Purpose: Full team alignment, celebrate wins, address cross-department issues, maintain team connection. Agenda: Time Topic Details 5 min Wins &amp; Shoutouts Celebrate completed work, client feedback, team wins 10 min Department Updates Quick update from each dept (Ops, Marketing, Dev, Finance) 10 min Client Pipeline &amp; Status Active clients, upcoming launches, new inquiries 10 min Cross-Dept Issues Issues needing multiple departments, decisions to make 5 min Announcements &amp; Close Company news, upcoming events, action items recap Required Output: Meeting notes posted to team Lark channel within 1 hour /* 4. Ad-Hoc / As-Needed Meetings */ 4 . Ad-Hoc / As-Needed Meetings When: As needed — scheduled same day or 24h in advance Who: Only people who need to be there (keep it small) When to call an ad-hoc meeting: Urgent client issue that needs immediate discussion Blocker that can&apos;t wait until next scheduled meeting Complex problem that needs real-time collaboration Decision that requires multiple people&apos;s input Rules for ad-hoc meetings: Must have a clear purpose stated in the invite Keep to 15-30 min max Document outcome/decision in relevant Lark channel If it can be resolved async (Lark message), don&apos;t meet /* 5. Monthly Performance Review */ 5 . Monthly Performance Review When: Last week of each month (45-60 min per person) Agenda: Review scorecard results (10 min) — Walk through 4 components Discuss wins (10 min) — What went well, recognize achievements Discuss growth areas (15 min) — Where to improve, support needed Set next month focus (10 min) — 1-2 specific development goals Employee feedback (10 min) — Their input on support, processes, team Required Output: Completed Monthly Evaluation form saved to employee file /* 6. Quarterly Planning Session */ 6 . Quarterly Planning Session When: First week of Jan, Apr, Jul, Oct (2-3 hours) Agenda: Review last quarter (30 min) — What worked, what didn&apos;t, key metrics Company updates (15 min) — Business health, new clients, changes Quarter goals (45 min) — Set 3-5 company priorities for next 90 days Team goals (30 min) — How each role supports company goals Process improvements (20 min) — What to start, stop, continue Open discussion (20 min) — Team input, questions, ideas Required Output: Quarterly Goals document shared with team within 48 hours /* 7. Meeting Rules */ 7 . Meeting Rules (All Meetings) /* DO Card */ ✓ DO • Start on time (don&apos;t wait for latecomers) • End with clear action items (who, what, when) • Camera ON for video calls • Record all client meetings • Post AI summary within 24h (client meetings) /* DON'T Card */ ✗ DON&apos;T • Hold meetings without an agenda • Let meetings run over without permission • Multitask (check phone, work on other things) • Skip meetings without notice • Schedule meetings without checking calendars /* Footer */ Owner: Operations Coordinator ); meeting cadence schedule meetings standup daily weekly monthly huddle sync one on one 1:1 team meeting"
